20010814.1919
Botulism, chili - USA (Texas): recall
20010904.2116
Date: 30 Oct 2001 03:16
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Canada Newswire via COMTEX [edited

The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) and INDIANLife Food
Corporation are warning the public not to consume INDIANLife brand
Roti Wraps and 6 varieties of Naan Breads. It is possible that these
products may support growth of bacteria responsible for botulism in
humans. These products should not be consumed.
All Best Before codes of the following products are affected by this
alert.
1. Coriander & Herbs Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 77762 00120 9
2. Garlic Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 7762 00102 5
3. Onion Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 77762 00100 1
4. Spinach Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 77762 00121 6
5. Tandoori Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 77762 00101 8
6. Whole Wheat Naan, 500 g, UPC 7 77762 00110 0
7. Roti Wraps, 250 g, UPC 7 77762 00108 7
These products manufactured by INDIANLife Food Corp., Burnaby, British
Columbia, have been distributed in British Columbia, Alberta,
Saskatchewan, and Manitoba. The manufacturer is voluntarily recalling
the affected products from the marketplace.
There have been no reported illnesses associated with the consumption
of these products.
Foods contaminated with _C. botulinum_ bacteria may not look or smell
spoiled. Botulism is a life-threatening illness caused by toxins
produced by _Clostridium botulinum_ bacteria. Consumers should dispose
of remaining product immediately or return products to the point of
purchase for a refund.
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency is monitoring the effectiveness of
the recall.
For more information, consumers and industry can call INDIANLife Food
Corporation or the CFIA at one of the following numbers:
INDIANLife Food Corporation
Rakesh Raniga
604-205-9176
CFIA
In the province of Quebec 1-800-561-3350; or
In other provinces and territories 1-800-442-2342.
